                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=anarancio",
                        "name": "anarancio",
                        "displayName": "Alejandro Narancio",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "just a note, I am using a MySQL database.. the database has a size of 550mb (aprox).\n\nIf I change the configuration and point to a database with the same structure but with no more than 100mb everything works fine.\n\nhere is how I configure the adapter:\n\n$pdoParams = array(\n    PDO::MYSQL_ATTR_USE_BUFFERED_QUERY => true\n);\n\n$params = array(\n    'host'           => 'localhost',\n    'username'       => 'root',\n    'password'       => '',\n    'dbname'         => 'test',\n    'driver_options' => $pdoParams\n);\n\n$db = Zend_Db::factory('Pdo_Mysql', $params);\nZend_Registry::set('db',$db);",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=anarancio",
                        "name": "anarancio",
                        "displayName": "Alejandro Narancio",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-01T10:53:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-01T10:53:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32674",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It seems like you have other issues here, please reopen if you can identify this as a ZF issue.\n\nIn your code, you are not actually connecting to the database in question (you have not called getConnection() on the adapter or sent a query).",
